title._content: Woman Crosses the Street at Cottonwood Falls, Kansas, near Emporia. She Is One of Many Spectators Who Come to the Town for the Annual Flint Hills Rodeo and Parade...06/1974

description._content: Original Caption: Woman Crosses the Street at Cottonwood Falls, Kansas, near Emporia. She Is One of Many Spectators Who Come to the Town for the Annual Flint Hills Rodeo and Parade. It Is a 19th Century "Cowboy" Town near a Possible Site for a Tall Grass Prairie National Park. The Rodeo Is a Major Cultural Event of the Area. Horses and Large Cattle Trucks Are the Featured Models of Transportation 06/1974 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-14587 Photographer: Duncan, Patricia D., 1932- Subjects: Emporia (Lyon county, Kansas, United States) inhabited place Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=557039 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
